To get a solution to forward.9, it is the exact set of conditions
as in forward.8, the lower deformable roll case. This case simply
has a rigid lower roll, so some of the conditions on sset 2 are
different than in the TALE memo.   However, the startup procedure
is basically the same.  On the release of the upstream meniscus
we can do by applying a much larger backpressure at a nip of
0.02 cm.   That backpressure is about 23000 dyn/cm2.   Otherwise,
follow CAREFULLY everything the TALE roll coating tutorial says.

After you get a solution, you can lower the backpressure as you squeeze
the rolls or change the speeds.  
